		<title>17LOCAL HISTORY</title>
		<content>     Some thoughts from Class 2on an   
 ancient cottage that collapsed in the 
 School Lane in 1982.                  
  "I am a cottage, small but tough,    
   My master doesn't care-             
   I am alone,                         
   I am falling to bits.               
   My slates are falling to the ground,
   The roof is broken                  
   Everything is broken.               
   Birds keep flying into me           
   My bricks are falling to the ground,
   What am I? I am half a cottage.     
   My room is a tip, my fire is out,   
   A bulldozer comes to knock me down, 
   A thousand bricks have fallen."     
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       </content>
